**Current behavior**

When parameter name is same as class name, and `super` used, it transform into invalid code.

- [REPL](https://babeljs.io/repl#?browsers=defaults%2C%20not%20ie%2011%2C%20not%20ie_mob%2011&build=&builtIns=false&spec=false&loose=false&code_lz=AQ4YwGwQwZx4BiB7JwDeAoUoC2BTAFwAskATACmSQEp0ttQAnQgV0YDtgYWAHPRgHT5iZSimoBuetgC-04DKA&debug=false&forceAllTransforms=false&shippedProposals=false&circleciRepo=&evaluate=false&fileSize=false&timeTravel=false&sourceType=module&lineWrap=true&presets=env%2Ces2015%2Cenv&prettier=false&targets=&version=7.11.4&externalPlugins=)


**Input Code**

```js
    class Foo {
      method(Foo) {
        return super.method(Foo);
      }
    }
```

**Expected behavior**


```js
  // ...

  _createClass(Foo, [{
    key: "method",
    value: function method(Foo) {
      return _get(_getPrototypeOf(Foo.prototype), "method", this).call(this, Foo);
                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ This is not right
    }
  }]);

  // ...
```

